17:55.440 --> 18:00.000
that actually constitute problems you could solve and address

18:00.080 --> 18:02.240
if you put your mind to it in the real world.

18:02.320 --> 18:05.760
And there's psychological reasons for assuming...

18:05.840 --> 18:09.520
One of the things you see when people's lives go seriously astray

18:09.600 --> 18:11.920
is that they don't generally...

18:12.000 --> 18:15.040
People generally don't run off a cliff

18:15.120 --> 18:17.440
immediately after doing brilliantly.

18:17.520 --> 18:20.160
What happens is they make one error,

18:20.240 --> 18:21.920
and then they make a more serious error,

18:21.920 --> 18:24.160
and then they repeat that 10,000 times,

18:24.240 --> 18:25.920
and then they're in hell.

18:26.000 --> 18:33.520
And it was their failure to rectify the mini-crisis

18:33.600 --> 18:37.520
all along the way that brings upon the apocalypse in their life.

18:37.600 --> 18:40.640
And I do see a lot of that political posturing

18:40.720 --> 18:43.760
characterizing the modern world,

18:43.840 --> 18:47.280
that people act out the role of world-redeeming savior,

18:47.360 --> 18:50.480
but they're not actually attending to genuine problems

18:50.480 --> 18:53.360
that are right in front of them that they could address

18:53.440 --> 18:56.640
if they acted responsibly.

18:56.720 --> 18:58.960
And then the final theme you developed, you said...

18:59.040 --> 19:00.160
This is very interesting.

19:00.240 --> 19:06.160
You said that the notion of natural disaster,

19:06.240 --> 19:09.520
in some sense, is ill-conceptualized

19:09.600 --> 19:15.200
because there's an ambiguity

19:15.280 --> 19:17.360
about whether, when a disaster occurs,

19:17.440 --> 19:20.800
it's a consequence of the hand of God,

19:20.880 --> 19:24.080
say, in the earthquake or the flood,

19:24.160 --> 19:26.800
or the utter failure of the authorities

19:26.880 --> 19:30.240
to have prepared properly for a foreseeable disaster.

19:30.320 --> 19:34.960
I thought this very clearly when Katrina hit New Orleans

19:35.040 --> 19:39.040
because a hue and cry went up about the catastrophe

19:39.120 --> 19:40.320
of the natural disaster,

19:40.400 --> 19:43.280
but you didn't have to dig very far before you realized

19:43.360 --> 19:46.080
that the reason that that hurricane

19:46.080 --> 19:47.920
was so devastating in New Orleans

19:48.000 --> 19:51.360
was because, well, the dykes hadn't been maintained

19:51.440 --> 19:55.120
and they'd only been built to withstand a one-in-one-century flood

19:55.200 --> 19:59.040
and that the entire infrastructure of the society was corrupt.

19:59.120 --> 20:02.880
And so, you know, in mythological representations,

20:02.960 --> 20:05.920
in deep narratives, there is an identity

20:06.000 --> 20:10.000
between the evil king and the wicked queen of nature.

20:10.080 --> 20:11.680
They're the same thing.

20:11.760 --> 20:13.840
And so if the king gets wicked enough,

20:13.840 --> 20:16.320
the evil queen of nature arises.

20:16.400 --> 20:19.520
And that's a representation of the fact that

20:19.600 --> 20:21.840
if your state is corrupt,

20:21.920 --> 20:26.240
natural disaster will definitely make itself shown

20:26.320 --> 20:28.160
and that you actually can't distinguish.

20:28.240 --> 20:30.560
There's no distinction between lack of preparation

20:30.640 --> 20:32.880
and a natural disaster in the final analysis.

20:32.960 --> 20:39.520
And corruption and blindness facilitate that nexus.

20:39.600 --> 20:41.680
So the Egyptians had a story.

20:41.760 --> 20:44.320
It's the story upon which their whole culture was funded

20:44.400 --> 20:47.520
that the state corrupted, that's Osiris.

20:47.600 --> 20:52.160
The state corrupted and became willfully blind as it aged.

20:52.240 --> 20:54.800
And then it was overthrown by, that's Osiris,

20:54.880 --> 20:57.600
is overthrown by Seth, who's the precursor of Satan,

20:57.680 --> 20:58.880
and then he rules.

20:58.960 --> 21:00.800
So now the tyrant rules.

21:00.880 --> 21:04.080
And then Isis, who's the queen of the underworld,

21:04.160 --> 21:05.040
she's nature.

21:05.120 --> 21:09.200
She makes herself known again, chaos, right?

21:09.200 --> 21:13.840
With enough disintegration at the sociological level,

21:13.920 --> 21:16.400
then chaos makes itself manifest again.

21:16.480 --> 21:19.040
It's one of the most ancient stories of mankind,

21:19.120 --> 21:21.840
playing out that dichotomy between the tyrant

21:21.920 --> 21:25.280
and natural disaster that you just described.

21:25.360 --> 21:29.840
Let me take those points in order if I can.

21:29.920 --> 21:32.480
I think that the most interesting thing to me

21:32.560 --> 21:37.600
about fantasies, about the end of the world,

21:37.680 --> 21:41.040
about the various millenarian cults through history,

21:41.120 --> 21:45.760
is that they are often accompanied by certain forms

21:45.840 --> 21:49.920
of behavior that one might characterize as ascetic.

21:50.000 --> 21:52.480
So the asceticism is an important part

21:52.560 --> 21:56.640
of many religious and secular movements.

21:56.720 --> 22:02.240
So the end is approaching, the apocalypse is nearing,

22:02.320 --> 22:06.560
and therefore we should fast, or perhaps even flog ourselves,

22:06.640 --> 22:09.760
like the flagellant orders at the time of the Black Death.

22:09.840 --> 22:14.480
And it seemed to me very interesting how many similar patterns

22:14.560 --> 22:18.320
one could see in our time.

22:18.400 --> 22:22.240
Whether you are preoccupied with climate change

22:22.320 --> 22:24.960
or systemic racism doesn't matter.

22:25.040 --> 22:30.320
You should engage in some kind of ascetic atonement

22:30.400 --> 22:33.120
in advance of the Great Reckoning.

22:33.200 --> 22:40.160
And this, I think, infests a lot of contemporary progressivism.

22:40.240 --> 22:44.320
The desire to eat rabbit food,

22:44.400 --> 22:50.960
to be constantly trying to eliminate things from one's diets.

22:51.040 --> 22:58.000
The desire to engage in abstention from reproduction.

22:58.080 --> 23:02.720
We must have children because climate change is so cataclysmic.

23:02.800 --> 23:05.120
So you have these sorts of ascetic behaviors

23:05.200 --> 23:08.960
which you can find in medieval and ancient religion.

23:09.040 --> 23:11.920
So I think that's an important first point.

23:12.000 --> 23:16.720
The second point is that mythology of the sort you describe

23:16.800 --> 23:20.080
in the case of the ancient Egyptian myths

23:20.160 --> 23:23.520
makes a lot of sense if you imagine yourself living

23:23.600 --> 23:27.200
in the prehistoric or very ancient world.

23:27.280 --> 23:31.440
Life expectancy was very short.

23:31.440 --> 23:34.240
Individuals were extraordinarily at risk

23:34.320 --> 23:39.600
from a whole variety of premature forms of mortality.

23:39.680 --> 23:42.160
And the natural world was deeply mysterious

23:42.240 --> 23:46.000
because there was no scientific framework for understanding

23:46.080 --> 23:51.200
anything, the fluctuations in the level of the River Nile,

23:51.280 --> 23:57.360
the periodic droughts that afflicted early agricultural societies.

23:57.440 --> 24:00.880
And so you end up with ways of making sense of

24:00.880 --> 24:05.600
an extraordinarily cruel and capricious world.

24:05.680 --> 24:10.560
So I think that's an important reason why myths persist.

24:10.640 --> 24:16.480
They're deeply rooted in our pre-modern experience.

24:16.560 --> 24:22.960
And I think that if one tries to think about our present predicament,

24:23.040 --> 24:29.440
it's odd that such things have such enduring power over us

24:29.520 --> 24:32.640
because since the scientific revolution and the Enlightenment,

24:32.720 --> 24:36.800
we have a much better handle on the challenges

24:36.880 --> 24:42.240
that a species like ours faces on a planet like ours.

24:42.320 --> 24:46.640
So what's odd is that despite having really quite a good understanding

24:46.720 --> 24:53.280
of, say, infectious disease or the ways that hurricanes

24:53.360 --> 24:56.240
strike the Eastern seaboard of the United States,

24:56.240 --> 25:01.520
we seem to be getting worse at handling pandemics and hurricanes.

25:01.600 --> 25:04.560
And that's a really important argument that the book makes.

25:04.640 --> 25:07.600
Compared with the generation of the 1950s,

25:07.680 --> 25:10.560
the generation of the 2010s and 2020s

25:10.640 --> 25:13.280
seemed really quite bad at disaster management

25:13.360 --> 25:16.480
in most Western societies, not only the United States.

25:16.560 --> 25:19.840
It's explaining that that takes us into new territory

25:19.920 --> 25:23.280
because I don't think you can explain the diminishing competence

25:23.360 --> 25:28.160
of the modern state without having a theory of its degeneration.

25:28.240 --> 25:32.080
And that's something that is a really important part of the book.

25:32.160 --> 25:35.760
Okay, so I want to pick up on two of those topics.

25:35.840 --> 25:44.080
So the first is you point out that as the apocalyptic vision predominates,

25:44.160 --> 25:46.640
there's a turn to asceticism.

25:46.720 --> 25:50.000
And then you describe, we could say, veganism and vegetarianism.

25:50.000 --> 25:53.520
And the insistence by the environmentalists

25:53.600 --> 25:55.440
that we must engage in degrowth

25:55.520 --> 25:57.520
and that we must produce our standard of living.

25:57.600 --> 26:04.560
And yes, okay, but there's a very interesting psychological rationale

26:04.640 --> 26:12.640
for that as well, which is that if the old state of being has become corrupt,

26:12.720 --> 26:13.680
so that's the old king.

26:13.760 --> 26:17.600
And now we're threatened by its collapse,

26:17.600 --> 26:26.240
then the proper thing to do is to engage in repentance and atonement

26:26.320 --> 26:32.480
because what you want to do is you want to offer up your stupid preconceptions

26:32.560 --> 26:36.240
to be destroyed so that you can rectify the corruption

26:36.320 --> 26:38.640
so that you can stave off the disaster.

26:38.720 --> 26:44.560
And so now it's interesting because with the millenarian

26:44.640 --> 26:46.400
and apocalyptic movements on the left,

26:46.480 --> 26:49.040
you have a simultaneous insistence

26:49.120 --> 26:55.280
that all sorts of impulsive, pleasure-seeking, licentious behavior

26:55.360 --> 26:59.040
should be centered and prioritized and celebrated.

26:59.120 --> 27:01.520
But at the same time, you have this insistence

27:01.600 --> 27:05.360
that there's a certain kind of asceticism that's also necessary.

27:05.440 --> 27:07.680
And I see in that as a psychologist,

27:07.760 --> 27:14.080
I see that as a proper mechanism of repair gone astray.

27:14.400 --> 27:21.360
Is that, well, you should always be cutting back in this ascetic way

27:21.440 --> 27:27.120
on your idiot excesses locally to improve the manner

27:27.200 --> 27:28.560
in which you conceptualize the world.

27:28.640 --> 27:31.200
That's the continual sacrificial offering

27:31.280 --> 27:34.240
of your own insufficiency and your own stupidity.

27:34.320 --> 27:37.360
And that does renew the world.

27:37.440 --> 27:40.400
And so, but now we've got this dynamic

27:40.480 --> 27:44.240
where we globalize the apocalypse.

27:44.320 --> 27:46.320
We view the end of the world.

27:46.400 --> 27:50.880
We assume that nothing but a kind of universal asceticism

27:50.960 --> 27:52.960
and atonement will suffice.

27:53.040 --> 27:55.840
That enables us to set local concerns aside,

27:55.920 --> 27:58.400
as we already discussed, and to act irresponsibly.

27:58.480 --> 28:03.280
And maybe that's part of what's producing this inability

28:03.280 --> 28:08.880
to actually respond locally and effectively to genuine problems.

28:08.960 --> 28:10.560
You know, in the Old Testament,

28:10.640 --> 28:16.160
there's a second commandment is to not use God's name in vain.

28:16.240 --> 28:18.640
And what that means, as far as I can tell,

28:18.720 --> 28:22.320
is that you shouldn't claim divine motivation

28:22.400 --> 28:25.360
for doing things that are actually self-serving.

28:25.440 --> 28:27.280
You shouldn't attribute sacred motivations

28:27.360 --> 28:33.120
to your own instrumental, impulsive, and self-serving behavior.

28:33.200 --> 28:35.280
And then that's echoed in the New Testament

28:35.360 --> 28:38.000
with the insistence that you shouldn't pray in public.

28:38.080 --> 28:41.840
Now, if you take on the apocalyptic burden and you're virtuous

28:41.920 --> 28:47.680
only in consequence of your compassionate concern,

28:47.760 --> 28:51.920
it gives you a perfect excuse to dispense with local responsibility.

28:52.000 --> 28:54.160
And if you dispense with local responsibility,

28:54.240 --> 28:56.880
then you're no longer able to engage

28:56.960 --> 28:59.280
in the concrete problem-solving activities

28:59.360 --> 29:00.560
of the sort that you described.

29:00.640 --> 29:03.920
I mean, what did you conclude when you have a chapter

29:04.000 --> 29:05.840
on developing political incompetence

29:05.920 --> 29:10.080
and also one on a sort of a belief in scientism?

29:10.160 --> 29:12.080
And that seems to me to be part of your attempt

29:12.160 --> 29:15.120
to assess the local failure

29:15.200 --> 29:17.680
while we're concentrating on the global apocalypse.

29:17.760 --> 29:19.280
And so what do you make of that,

29:19.360 --> 29:23.360
that concatenation of causal forces?

29:23.360 --> 29:26.720
There are two things that are going on, I think.

29:26.800 --> 29:32.960
One is that the more people refer to the science,

29:33.040 --> 29:35.920
the more you should suspect that they are engaged

29:36.000 --> 29:39.680
in some quasi-religious activity.

29:39.760 --> 29:43.920
Because the notion of some settled body of knowledge

29:44.000 --> 29:46.960
called the science is at odds with the reality

29:47.040 --> 29:50.400
of the scientific method, which is a constant struggle

29:50.480 --> 29:53.280
to falsify hypotheses through experimentation.

29:54.880 --> 29:58.080
During the COVID-19 pandemic, but I think it predates it,

29:58.160 --> 30:00.240
it was already going on in debates about climate,

30:00.320 --> 30:03.520
there was a lot of spurious invocation of the science.

30:04.240 --> 30:08.880
And one might as well have been saying the gods or the deity,

30:08.960 --> 30:13.440
because it was, in fact, quite unscientific thinking

30:13.520 --> 30:14.160
that was going on.

30:14.240 --> 30:15.760
I'll give you an illustration of this.

30:16.560 --> 30:20.560
A great delusion is to imagine that we can prevent

30:20.640 --> 30:24.320
the rise of average temperatures by large scale

30:24.400 --> 30:25.760
asceticism in the West.

30:26.800 --> 30:29.760
We must give up internal combustion engines.

30:29.840 --> 30:31.920
We should give up eating meat and so on.

30:32.640 --> 30:37.840
If we end up buying electric vehicles and solar cells

30:37.920 --> 30:41.840
manufactured in China with electricity generated

30:41.920 --> 30:44.240
by burning ever larger quantities of coal,

30:44.800 --> 30:49.040
the probability of reducing average temperatures is zero.

30:50.320 --> 30:55.200
Because that is, in fact, the perfect illustration

30:55.840 --> 30:58.720
of wrongheadedness in action.

30:59.680 --> 31:03.040
If one accepts the premises of the debates

31:03.120 --> 31:05.280
on the causes of rising temperatures,

31:05.360 --> 31:09.120
it makes no sense at all for us to behave this way.

31:09.200 --> 31:11.520
Our asceticism will make no difference

31:12.080 --> 31:15.600
if it manifests itself as increased burning of coal in China.

31:15.680 --> 31:17.200
So that's the first thing that's going on.

31:17.280 --> 31:20.640
I mean, like, well, or increased burning in coal in Germany,

31:20.720 --> 31:23.440
because that's what's happened with the Green Revolution in Germany.

31:23.520 --> 31:24.000
Exactly.

31:24.080 --> 31:27.840
They shut off the nuclear plants and started up the Lignite plant.

31:27.920 --> 31:33.920
So this kind of wrongheadedness leads to all kinds of policy errors

31:34.000 --> 31:38.000
because people have focused on the satisfaction of asceticism,

31:38.000 --> 31:42.960
the virtue signaling that comes with getting rid of nuclear power stations

31:43.040 --> 31:45.040
or internal combustion engines.

31:45.120 --> 31:47.440
So there's a kind of generalized failure,

31:47.520 --> 31:51.280
which embraces the policy elite to think rationally

31:51.360 --> 31:54.080
about the problems that we're trying to address.

31:54.160 --> 31:56.640
The second problem, which I think is just as important,

31:56.720 --> 31:58.960
is the way the administrative state functions.

31:59.680 --> 32:01.840
If you compare central governments today

32:01.920 --> 32:05.520
with their counterparts of half a century or 70 years ago,

32:05.520 --> 32:06.880
they've become much larger.

32:06.960 --> 32:09.920
They're bloated in terms of the numbers of people employed.

32:10.720 --> 32:12.800
They intervene in many more ways.

32:14.880 --> 32:19.040
There's an enormous corpus of regulation in all western countries.

32:20.240 --> 32:25.040
This administrative state, unwieldy regulatory, is very inefficient.

32:25.120 --> 32:28.160
It's very bad at achieving its intended goals.

32:29.120 --> 32:31.840
That has to do with the way that bureaucracy works

32:31.920 --> 32:36.160
and the sclerotic tendencies that the modern state suffers from.

32:36.240 --> 32:41.680
So between the science as a quasi-religious way of thinking

32:42.400 --> 32:44.000
and the administrative state,

32:44.080 --> 32:46.560
we have a very, very dysfunctional approach

32:46.640 --> 32:49.200
to nearly all the problems that confront us.

32:49.280 --> 32:51.920
And that is really the central argument of doom.

32:52.000 --> 32:54.480
It's very significant that in our lifetimes,

32:55.200 --> 32:58.880
governments have got worse at dealing with disasters, not better.

32:58.960 --> 33:01.280
Despite the accumulation of scientific knowledge,

33:01.280 --> 33:05.520
we seem somehow, collectively, to be worse at scientific thinking.

