42:45.520 --> 42:48.640
I'm always impressed by the presence

42:48.720 --> 42:52.640
of the self-appointed elect in academic life.

42:52.720 --> 42:56.080
People who have a sense that they are morally superior

42:56.160 --> 42:59.600
to those around them, they do belong to an elite.

42:59.680 --> 43:06.480
And their behavior should be, as it were, fitting to that preeminence.

43:06.560 --> 43:09.280
Now, I am a kind of Calvinist atheist.

43:09.360 --> 43:10.720
I come from the west of Scotland

43:10.800 --> 43:13.600
where that kind of thinking was very well established.

43:13.680 --> 43:17.440
I can see the people who think they belong to the elect

43:17.520 --> 43:21.040
all around me in American academic life.

43:21.120 --> 43:23.760
And, of course, the critical idea

43:23.840 --> 43:27.120
which Robert Louis Stevenson gets at in the Master of Ballon Trey

43:27.200 --> 43:30.960
and James Hogg gets in the Confessions of a Justified Sinner

43:31.040 --> 43:33.200
is that the elect are the worst people.

43:33.280 --> 43:36.560
It's the people who think that they belong to the elite

43:36.640 --> 43:39.920
