and it was much worse than the hypothetical crisis itself.

46:05.920 --> 46:09.360
But what I wanted to focus on was the reason

46:09.440 --> 46:12.080
that that overreach occurs.

46:12.160 --> 46:16.800
Now, I've been writing a book about biblical narratives,

46:16.880 --> 46:18.160
so they're very much on my mind,

46:18.240 --> 46:19.760
and that's partly why I'm bringing them up.

46:19.840 --> 46:23.520
But I talked to a good friend of mine and his brother,

46:23.600 --> 46:26.560
Jonathan Pascio and Matthew Pascio,

46:26.640 --> 46:31.600
about the first apocalyptic cataclysm

46:31.680 --> 46:33.760
as it's laid out in the book of Genesis,

46:33.840 --> 46:38.000
and that's the Sin of Eve and the Consequent Sin of Adam.

46:38.080 --> 46:41.920
