01:04:21.920 --> 01:04:25.040
And then you turned to a particular concept of ultimate right,

01:04:25.120 --> 01:04:30.640
which was a form of extreme self-sacrifice with no public acclaim.

01:04:30.720 --> 01:04:33.040
I gotta say, those are strange things for someone

01:04:33.120 --> 01:04:36.800
who also said during the same discussion,

01:04:37.600 --> 01:04:39.840
who proclaimed a kind of central atheism,

01:04:39.920 --> 01:04:42.960
because I can't help seeing echoes in that of,

01:04:43.600 --> 01:04:45.600
while the Christian passion, for example,

01:04:45.680 --> 01:04:50.240
is that you're called upon to do right at your own expense,

01:04:50.320 --> 01:04:52.320
even your own ultimate expense,

01:04:52.400 --> 01:04:55.520
with no hope of public acclaim,

01:04:55.600 --> 01:05:00.080
and you do that in the service of something that's ultimately right.

01:05:00.800 --> 01:05:06.000
And so, well, that's a parallel that occurred to me

01:05:06.080 --> 01:05:07.040
when you made the argument.

01:05:07.120 --> 01:05:08.240
That's a perfectly shrewd observation.

